You could even formalize this as part of the execution stack:

Inference Hygiene: Clearly distinguish observations, interpretations, hypotheses, and validated conclusions.

That makes the system more transparent and reduces the chance that it quietly optimizes for assumptions instead of the user’s actual objectives.

